<Layout title="Attorneys · Florida Attorney Partner Hub — Closings, Title Work, FIRPTA, Estate Planning, Asset Protection &amp; Homestead Specialist" description="Florida attorney partner hub educating buyers, sellers, and HNW clients on what attorneys do in real estate transactions: closing execution at title company or law firm in Florida attorney closing state counties; title search and title insurance coordination through ALTA or Florida-form policies; FR/Bar contract review and negotiation under Florida Realtors and Florida Bar joint forms; Florida deed type selection including warranty deed providing full title warranty, quit-claim deed providing no warranty, lady bird or enhanced life estate deed for probate avoidance with retained control, trust transfer deed for revocable trust ownership, special warranty deed for limited warranty conveyances; FIRPTA Foreign Investment in Real Property Tax Act withholding compliance under IRC Section 1445 with generally 15% gross purchase price withholding on foreign-seller transactions and reduced rates available with IRS Form 8288-B certification with attorney coordination on Form 8288 submission within 20 days of closing; Florida homestead exemption under Florida Constitution Article X Section 4 with UNLIMITED creditor protection on primary residence and descendant restrictions on devise; estate planning coordination through revocable trust ownership structures with Florida homestead-compliant designation; asset protection through tenancy by entireties Florida-protected marital ownership and LLC structures and FLP family limited partnership structures; equitable distribution coordination for divorce-related real estate transactions under Florida Statutes Chapter 61; lender attorney coordination at closing for deed and security instrument execution. Florida attorney types: real estate transactional attorney handling closings and contract review and title work and deed preparation; title attorney handling title search and title insurance underwriting and title defect resolution and ALTA + Florida-form policies; estate planning attorney handling trust formation and will drafting and beneficiary designation and Florida homestead-compliant trust ownership and lady bird deed; family law divorce attorney handling equitable distribution and marital vs non-marital property classification and refinance / sale coordination during divorce; asset protection attorney handling tenancy by entireties and LLC ownership and Florida homestead unlimited exemption strategy and FLP structures. Florida Bar credentials: Florida Bar Board Certified Real Estate Lawyer; Florida Bar Real Property Probate & Trust Law Section RPPTL; Florida Bar Family Law Section; Florida Bar Tax Section; ABA Real Property Trust & Estate Section RPTE; CELA Certified Elder Law Attorney through National Elder Law Foundation; LLM in Taxation Master of Laws post-JD specialty degree from NYU Georgetown or U Florida. Partner-as-borrower CTA at bottom routing attorneys to dedicated attorney mortgage guide covering BigLaw partner W-2 + K-1 + capital distributions + RSU multi-source synthesis under Fannie Mae B3-3.4-02, regional firm partnership distributions, and solo or regional Schedule C income with Bank Statement Non-QM alternative." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/attorneys/">
